    "summary": "I worked within Philips for over 52 years, having served in three different Product Divisions of Philips. I started working in the Healthcare Industry in January 1977, joining Medical Applications, a joint venture of Philips and Siemens.\n\nI have spent 18 years as an Field Service Engineer and 12 years as a District Service Manager. During the last 18 years, I have served as SAP Business Process Analyst, SAP Helpdesk Manager, Call Centre Manager, IT Manager, SAP Project Manager, Business Applications (ERP) Support Manager and Business & Service Demand Manager.  From 2007 to 2009, I worked in the Netherlands on a global installed base project as a team lead.\n\nIn August of 2010, I moved to Singapore to work in the APAC Cluster CS Operations group as a Business Process Analyst.\n\nIn August of 2015, I moved to Eindhoven, Netherlands, to take up a position of Business Process Expert in the area of product Installed Base and Recall processes, with Global Customer Service.  I have been the Installed Base Process Expert for a period of more than five years.\n\nIn March of 2021, I provided Project Management support and Installed Base process knowledge for an Interventional Device manufacturing unit of Philips. \n\nIn August of 2021, I started working as a freelance consultant, specializing in Healthcare ERP systems such as SAP, as well as service delivery applications such as Salesforce.\n\n\n\nSpecialties:\n\nField Service Engineer\nField Service Management\nInstalled Base Management\nGlobal Projects Team Leadership\nIT Service Delivery Management\nIT Project Management\nCall Centre Management\nSAP Helpdesk Support\nSAP Process Analyst\nSAP Project Management\nSAP Support Management\nSAP Security and Authorisations\nBusiness Process Analysis\nITIL Foundation Certification\nLean Six Sigma\nSalesforce Support",
